cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about deep learning for face verification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel loss function and deep feature learning method, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses normalization, which is a common technique in multimedia processing, suggesting that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses a mixture model, which is a common technique in statistical modeling, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
